Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

> If you know you're making this recipe in advance, take the @Pizza Dough{10%ounce} out
> of the fridge to come to room temperature.

Using your hands, stretch out the dough into a rough 1⁄4-inch thick rectangle.
Place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and prick all over with a #fork{}.
Place in the oven to par-bake for about ~{15%minutes}, until beginning to brown
on the edges.

> If you have a #rolling pin{} or #wine bottle{}, you can use it to roll out the
> dough on a lightly floured surface.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @Prosciutto{4%ounce}. Halve the
@Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @Fresh Mozzarella{8%ounce}.
Tear the @Basil{1%bunch} leaves.

Spread the par-baked flatbread with @Pesto{3%tablespoon} and top with the sliced
mozzarella, heirloom tomatoes, and prosciutto. Return to the oven until cheese
begins to bubble and prosciutto crisps, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Toss the @Arugula{2%ounce} with @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} and season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then sprinkle over the flatbread along with
the basil. Cut the flatbread into squares and enjoy!